If I had to sum this game up, it would be a cheap version of EVE: Valkyrie. But it is also a pretty good game in its own right. With several missions to complete as well as multiplayer battles and missions, there is lots here to keep you amused for a while at least. OK, so it doesn’t look amazing and the motion sickness will bring most people to the point of vomiting, but sit in a comfortable chair and you will soon believe you really are taking place in a giant space battle. This game makes it possible to be fully immersed within it and that is why it is worth a download. Space shooters simply work well in VR and the more the merrier.
Stuck in the tutorial phase, where asked to shoot down drones in the asteroid field: they are spawning endlessly... however, the idea is good - it lacks everything else.
review_feedback: You're playing the practice mode which is intentionally endless. There's a separate tutorial with an instructor who guides you through how to pilot the ship.

one_reviews_text: Played for a good hour. Felt like it had potential, but there was a multiplayer option and I think all the "players" were just bots? Set up my own lobby and no one entered in an entire 10/15 min round. There seemed to be "doors" to fly to (were marked as waypoints) but they didn't open/do anything. Most maps were limited to 1 big structure in the middle. Needed a touch more variety. Overall, it needs to be polished a little and it would be great.
